  "prompt": "What causes a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage?",
  "response": "A pulsating feeling under the left rib cage can be caused by a variety of factors. Some possible explanations include:\n\n1. **Muscle Spasms**: Strained muscles in the abdominal wall or diaphragm can create a pulsating sensation.\n\n2. **Gastrointestinal Issues**: Conditions such as gas, bloating, or constipation may lead to sensations that feel like pulsation.\n\n3. **Blood Vessel Pulsation**: The aorta, which carries blood from the heart, runs close to the left side of the abdomen. Sometimes, you may feel the pulse of the aorta, especially if you are thin or have increased blood flow.\n\n4. **Cardiac Causes**: Although less common, some heart conditions can cause referred sensations in the abdomen.\n\n5. **Spleen Issues**: The spleen is located on the left side, and conditions affecting it, such as splenomegaly (enlargement), can potentially cause discomfort or unusual sensations.\n\n6. **Pancreatitis**: Inflammation of the pancreas can lead to discomfort in the upper abdomen, which may be perceived as pulsating.\n\n7. **Nerve Irritation**: Conditions such as shingles or other nerve irritation can create unusual sensations in the area.\n\n8. **Anxiety or Stress**: Sometimes, anxiety can cause heightened awareness of bodily sensations, leading to the perception of pulsation.\n\nIf the sensation is persistent, painful, or accompanied by other symptoms (such as shortness of breath, chest pain, or significant discomfort), it is advisable to seek medical attention to rule out any serious underlying conditions.",
